text.tspan: Suicide rate by sex, World, 2000 to 2019
Annual number of suicides per 100,000 males or females. Suicide deaths are underreported in many countries due to social stigma and
cultural or legal concerns. This data is adjusted for this underreporting to estimate the actual rate of suicides.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory (2022)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
